    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="47"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 47 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CMWS1" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_THS1" type="to"
                            >Truman</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d47fn1">Sent by the United States Military Attaché, London,
                        via Army channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-01">1 June
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prime Minister to President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName>.
                    Personal and top secret. Number 63.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>I will gladly come to Berlin with a British delegation but I consider that
                        July 15, repeat July the month after June, is much too <pb facs="0223"
                            n="91" xml:id="pg_91"/> late for the urgent questions that demand
                        attention between us, and that we shall do an injury to world hopes and
                        unity if we allow personal or national requirements to stand in the way of
                        an earlier meeting. Although I am in the midst of a hotly-contested
                        election, I would not consider my tasks here as comparable to a meeting
                        between the three of us. I have proposed June 15, repeat June the month
                        before July, but if that is not possible why not July 1, 2, or 3?</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>I have sent a copy of this message to Premier <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2"
                            >Stalin</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d47fn2">See <hi rend="italic">
                                <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2">Stalin</persName>’s
                            Correspondence</hi>, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 362.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
